Enum UsageMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<UsageMode>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<UsageMode>

    public enum UsageMode
extends java.lang.Enum<UsageMode>
    Represents how a Structure can be used.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      CORNER

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • SAVE

        public static final UsageMode SAVE
        The mode used when saving a structure.

      • LOAD

        public static final UsageMode LOAD
        The mode used when loading a structure.

      • CORNER

        public static final UsageMode CORNER
        Used when saving a structure for easy size calculation. When using this mode, the Structure name MUST match the name in the second Structure block that is in SAVE.

      • DATA

        public static final UsageMode DATA
        Used to run specific custom functions, which can only be used for certain Structures. The structure block is removed after this function completes. The data tags (functions) can be found on the wiki.
